                <p dir="ltr">EA and DICE held their grand reveal for Battlefield 6 today, with streamers from around the world descending into Los Angeles to take their first crack at the game. Along with the first gameplay reveal came confirmation of BF6's PC requirements, and thankfully, you won't need a super-rig to get the best performance.</p><p dir="ltr">The minimum requirements to play Battlefield 6 on PC include a Nvidia RTX 2060 or AMD Radeon RX 5600 graphics card, as well as either an Intel Core i5-8400 or AMD Ryzen 5 2600 processor. Recommended specs don't venture much further than that, as the recommended graphics card is an RTX 3060Ti or Radeon RX 6700-XT, along with a i7 or Ryzen 7 processor.</p>



    
